&gt; We&#39;ve seen a couple of cases here in which the alexa-tools av_procarc
&gt; DAT file maker generates a DAT incorrectly, from Heritrix ARC files.
&gt; For a small number of records in the DATs, it may fail to prefix a
&gt; blank
&gt; line before the header line for the record, causing that record to be
&gt; lost in
&gt; CDX processing, and adding its attributes to the previous record&#39;s
&gt; (leading to incorrect ARC offsets and MIME types for the previous
&gt; item).
&gt;  
&gt; As far as I can possibly see, it&#39;s not related to the format of the ARC
&gt; itself; 
&gt; Heritrix is, I think, blameless.  Rather, it may be related to the
&gt; immediately 
&gt; preceding file containing a large number of embedded images and links,
&gt; 
&gt; creating a larger-than-normal DAT record.  I wonder whether anyone else
&gt; 
&gt; using the av_procarc tool might have detected this problem?  I have yet
&gt; to 
&gt; find any particular suspicious code in av_procarc, but haven&#39;t delved
&gt; very far.
&gt;  
&gt; The following Perl lunacy indicates how to fix a DAT file so afflicted.
&gt;  
&gt;   perl -pi -e &#39;undef $/;
&gt; s/([^&#92;n])&#92;n(https?:&#92;/&#92;/.*alexa&#92;/dat)/$1&#92;n&#92;n$2/g&#39; *dat
&gt;  
